    • Constructor Detail

      • ExponentialStops

        @SafeVarargs
public ExponentialStops(Float base,
                                     @NonNull
                                     Stop<I,O>... stops)
        Create exponential stops with an explicit base. Use through Stops.exponential(Stop[])
        Parameters:
        base - The exponential base of the interpolation curve. It controls the rate at which the function output increases. Higher values make the output increase more towards the high end of the range. With values close to 1 the output increases linearly.
        stops - the stops
